  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>The Repairs by Device report provides a list of items/services used to repair a particular device. This report pulls data based on the <strong>Used for Device</strong> Relations field when adding an item to a repair ticket.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153323.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"Reports:RepairsbyDevice-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933803762/Reports+Repairs+by+Technician\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933803762\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Repairs by Technician</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1939570735/Reports+Repairs+by+Technician+and+Item\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1939570735\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Repairs by Tech and Item</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153321.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h2 id=\"Reports:RepairsbyDevice-ViewingtheRepairsbyDeviceReport\">Viewing the Repairs by Device Report</h2><p /><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, click <strong>Reports</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153327.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>2. On the Reports page, click on the <strong>Productivity dropdown </strong>along the top row of report categories. From the available list, click <strong>Repairs by Device</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153330.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>3. Use the available filters to scope results based on the assigned parameters.\u00a0Once you have set your filters, click\u00a0<strong>Apply\u00a0Filters\u00a0</strong>to run the report.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153332.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><ul><li><p><strong>Date Range </strong>- Select a date range for your scope of results.</p></li><li><p><strong>Location </strong>- Select a specific location or an aggregate report of all locations.</p></li><li><p><strong>Ticket Status </strong>- Select a specific ticket status or all ticket statuses for your results. The results will reflect the date when the ticket was updated. By default, the report will run for tickets in <strong>Closed</strong> status because this is the most reliable method for this business model.</p></li><li><p><strong>Action</strong> - Filter results by any assigned Ticket Action(s).</p></li><li><p><strong>Resolution</strong> - Filter results by any assigned Ticket Resolution(s).</p></li><li><p><strong>Item Type</strong> - Select a specific item type or all item types.</p></li><li><p><strong>Catalog</strong>\u00a0<strong>Item</strong>\u00a0- Keyword search for a specific catalog item.</p></li><li><p><strong>Include Labor in Total Cost</strong> - Labor is added based on hours entered on ticket items and the assigned staff member's pay rate assigned in their profile.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Note</strong>: We recommend that you account for productivity based on closed tickets only. Once a ticket has been closed, the date will no longer change, and the ticket has been paid in full. This also aligns with our <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934360642/RepairQ+Accounting+Principles\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934360642\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Accounting Principles</a> , as open tickets are considered a liability until the ticket is closed.\u00a0</p><p /><p>4. (Optional) Click <strong>Hide/Show Filters\u00a0</strong>on the upper-right side of the page to collapse/expand the filters when viewing reports.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153336.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>5. (Optional) Click\u00a0<strong>To Excel\u00a0</strong>on the upper-right side of the report page to export an Excel-friendly document. The export will include any filtered data when running the report.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153339.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><h2 id=\"Reports:RepairsbyDevice-RepairsbyDevice\">Repairs by Device</h2><p>The Repairs by Device Report gives a list of Repair Devices and a breakdown of any parts and/or services added to the repair, quantities of added parts/services, and total Sales and Discounts on those items. The Profit Margin is calculated by the following equation: Gross Sale - Discounts - Total Cost = Profit Margin.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1933377814/image-20230627-153344.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
